                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a 25-year-old client who will undergo bilateral orchidectomy for testicular cancer. Which statement by the nurse would be helpful in exploring the client's concerns about loss of reproductive ability?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nOne of the most helpful approaches in exploring client concerns is to use open-ended questions. These tend to elicit more descriptive responses on the part of the client. Option 1 imposes the nurse's opinion on the client and does not value the client's perspective. Options 3 and 4 are closed-ended questions that may be answered with a \"yes\" or \"no\" response.",
                        "id": "b99e574a396c407d9c637b567fecda05",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    }
